  private:
    static emString GetCommonPath() -> emString
    static void TryDeleteDeadDirectories()
    void TryStartOwnDirectory()
    class IpcServerClass : public emMiniIpcServer (handles ping for liveness detection)

  Implementation detail: emTmpFile invents temporary file paths via emTmpFileMaster,
  which creates a per-process directory under a common tmp path. Dead directories
  from crashed processes are cleaned up by pinging their IPC servers via emMiniIpcServer.
  The path naming uses a hash of hostname+username for isolation. Destructor auto-deletes
  the file/directory tree. Depends on emModel, emMiniIpc, emInstallInfo.

C++ usage in emCore (0 usages outside emTmpFile.h/cpp):
  emTmpFile is not used by any other file in emCore.
  It is used outside emCore by:
    include/emTmpConv/emTmpConvModel.h
    src/emTest/emTestContainers.cpp

Rust equivalents found:
  - No direct port of emTmpFile or emTmpFileMaster found in Rust emCore.
  - No usage of the tempfile crate found in src/emCore/.
  - tests/behavioral/file_selection.rs has a custom TempDir struct (line 7-26) used
    only in tests, not in library code.
  - The tempfile crate is present in Cargo.lock (used by test dependencies).

Coverage gaps:
  - Entire emTmpFile class has no Rust port (5 public methods unported).
  - Entire emTmpFileMaster class has no Rust port (2 public methods unported).
  - The dead-directory cleanup via IPC ping mechanism has no Rust equivalent.
  - No consumer of emTmpFile exists in Rust emCore (consistent with C++ where it is
    only used by emTmpConv outside emCore).

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - When/if emTmpConv is ported, will it need the full emTmpFileMaster IPC-based
    cleanup mechanism, or will the tempfile crate's auto-cleanup suffice?
  - emTmpFile depends on emModel and emMiniIpc. The Rust port has emMiniIpc
    (src/emCore/emMiniIpc.rs). Does it have sufficient functionality to support
    emTmpFileMaster's liveness-ping pattern if needed?

